  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Supervisor",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a dedicated and experienced Construction Supervisor to oversee our civil engineering and building projects. You will be responsible for the day-to-day management of site activities, ensuring that all works are executed safely, on schedule, and in strict accordance with technical specifications and Singapore’s regulatory standards.<br /></p><p>Key Responsibilities</p><ul><li>Site Supervision: Oversee daily operations and manage a team of workers and subcontractors to ensure project milestones are met.</li><li>Safety Leadership: Enforce Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) regulations. Conduct daily toolbox meetings and ensure all personnel use appropriate PPE.</li><li>Quality Control: Conduct regular site inspections to ensure workmanship complies with CONQUAS standards and approved blueprints/technical drawings.</li><li>Coordination: Liaise with Project Managers, Architects, and Engineers to resolve site technicalities and resource bottlenecks.</li><li>Reporting: Maintain accurate daily site diaries, manpower logs, and progress reports for management review.</li><li>Resource Management: Monitor material deliveries and equipment usage to minimize wastage and maintain a tidy worksite.</li></ul><p><br />Skills & Attributes</p><ul><li>Technical Proficiency: Ability to read and interpret structural drawings and blueprints accurately.</li><li>Language: Proficiency in English is required for reporting; ability to speak a second language (e.g., Mandarin, Tamil, or Bengali) is helpful for worker communication.</li><li>Driver’s License: Possession of a valid Class 3 Driving License is highly preferred for travel between project sites.</li><li>Problem-Solving: Strong interpersonal skills with a \"can-do\" attitude to resolve on-site conflicts or delays.</li></ul>",
